672	        // rule DURING parsing: it expands each rule's `_restrict(φ)`
673	        // embedded restriction into a fresh `Restr_<rule>_<i>` restriction
674	        // (inserted before the rule) and rewrites the rule's actions to
675	        // reference it.  RS captures `_restrict` into
676	        // `Rule.embedded_restrictions` at parse time; run the equivalent
677	        // lifting pass here, BEFORE wellformedness / elaboration / rendering,
678	        // so the transformed parser theory drives all three (the renderer
679	        // iterates `parsed.items`).
