227	    /// `--maude-processes=M` — size of the pool of Maude subprocesses
228	    /// the rayon workers borrow from at parallel sites.  Each
229	    /// subprocess costs ~30-100 MB resident; too many → OOM on small
230	    /// VMs.  Default is `max(1, processors)` (a 1:1 workers:maudes
231	    /// ratio; forced to 1 when `--processors=1`), balancing throughput
232	    /// against memory.  `M=1` forces all workers to share one Maude
233	    /// (pre-pool behaviour, byte-identical to sequential).  When
234	    /// `--processors=1` we force `M=1` automatically (no point in a
235	    /// pool with no parallelism).  HS uses a single Maude per
236	    /// ClosedTheory — this pool is a Rust-specific implementation
237	    /// improvement to remove the IPC mutex contention bottleneck.
238	    pub maude_processes: Option<usize>,
239	
